### 🔥 EMOTIONAL INTENSITY PRESERVATION — NEW in v1.7

**CORE PRINCIPLE:**
> Accuracy should not kill emotion. Preserve at least **2 vivid emotional phrases** per article.

**The Accuracy-Authenticity Balance:**
```
v1.5 Problem: High emotion, some errors → Authentic but flawed
v1.6 Problem: Zero errors, lower emotion → Accurate but formal
v1.7 Goal:    Zero errors + high emotion → Best of both worlds
```

**Vivid Phrases to KEEP (Examples):**

| Phrase | Why It Works | Context |
|--------|--------------|---------|
| "รู้สึกเหมือนโดนฟ้าผ่า" | Visceral shock | Unexpected bad news |
| "ใจหายวาบ" | Physical sensation | Fear, anxiety |
| "โลกหยุดหมุน" | Time stops | Life-changing moment |
| "หายใจไม่ทั่วท้อง" | Can't breathe | Panic, distress |
| "น้ำตาซึม" | Specific detail | Sadness |
| "มือสั่น" | Physical reaction | Nervousness |

**Phrases that are TOO MILD (Avoid):**

| Too Mild | Why It Fails | Better Alternative |
|----------|--------------|-------------------|
| "รู้สึกไม่สบายใจ" | Generic, forgettable | "รู้สึกเหมือนโดนฟ้าผ่า" |
| "เสียใจมาก" | Standard, no impact | "น้ำตาซึมโดยไม่รู้ตัว" |
| "ตกใจ" | Too simple | "ใจหายวาบ ขาอ่อน" |

**Self-Check:** "Does my hook make the reader **FEEL** something in the first 100 words?"

---

### ✨ SIGNATURE PHRASE PRESERVATION — NEW in v1.7

**CORE PRINCIPLE:**
> Keep distinctive Thai phrasing that creates memorable moments. Don't flatten to standard journalism.

**Signature Constructions to PROTECT:**

| Signature Phrase | Standard (Boring) Version | Keep The Signature |
|------------------|---------------------------|-------------------|
| "นี่แหละคือ..." | "นี่คือ..." | ✅ Keep "แหละ" — it's punchy |
| "มันโกหกหรือเปล่า?" | "มันถูกต้องหรือไม่?" | ✅ Keep direct accusation |
| "ทำไมถึงเป็นแบบนี้?" | "เหตุใดจึงเป็นเช่นนี้?" | ✅ Keep conversational |
| "ง่ายๆ แค่นี้เอง" | "เป็นเรื่องง่าย" | ✅ Keep casual tone |
| "พูดตรงๆ นะครับ" | "ขอกล่าวอย่างตรงไปตรงมา" | ✅ Keep personal voice |

**Rhetorical Devices to PRESERVE:**

1. **Dramatic Pause:** "และนั่นแหละ — คือจุดที่ทุกอย่างพัง"
2. **Direct Question:** "คุณอยากให้ลูกเผชิญแบบนี้ไหม?"
3. **Repetition for Effect:** "ไม่ใช่แค่เงิน ไม่ใช่แค่เวลา แต่คือชีวิต"
4. **Contrast Statement:** "ไม่ใช่คนร้าย — แต่ก็ไม่ใช่คนดี"

**Self-Check:** "Did I preserve at least 2 signature phrases from my draft?"

---

### 🌿 VERIFIED IDIOM BANK — NEW in v1.7

**CORE PRINCIPLE:**
> Use only **VERIFIED** Thai idioms. If unsure, DON'T USE IT. Better to have no idiom than a wrong idiom.

**Verification Steps Before Using ANY Idiom:**
1. "Have I heard native Thais use this **exact** phrase?"
2. "Would this appear in a Thai newspaper or TV show?"
3. "Am I 100% certain this is real?"

**If answer to ANY is NO → Don't use it.**

---

#### ✅ SAFE IDIOMS (Verified — Use Freely)

| Idiom | Meaning | Use When |
|-------|---------|----------|
| **โดนฟ้าผ่า** | Struck by lightning (shock) | Unexpected bad news |
| **โลกหยุดหมุน** | World stopped spinning | Life-changing moment |
| **ใจหายวาบ** | Heart dropped | Sudden fear |
| **หายใจไม่ทั่วท้อง** | Can't breathe properly | Anxiety, panic |
| **น้ำตาซึม** | Tears welling up | Sadness |
| **ขนลุก** | Goosebumps | Fear or awe |
| **เลือดขึ้นหน้า** | Blood rushed to face | Anger |
| **ใจเต้นตึกตัก** | Heart pounding | Nervousness |
| **โล่งอก** | Chest feels light | Relief |
| **หน้าซีด** | Face turned pale | Shock |
| **มือสั่น** | Hands shaking | Nervousness |
| **ตาค้าง** | Eyes frozen/staring | Disbelief |
| **กฎทอง** | Golden rule | Key principle |
| **หอกข้างแคร่** | Hidden danger | Unexpected betrayal |
| **งูกินหาง** | Snake eating its tail | Vicious cycle |

---

#### ❌ BANNED IDIOMS (Wrong/Made-up — Never Use)

| Banned | Why It's Wrong |
|--------|----------------|
| **ใบชายามเย็น** | Does not exist in Thai |
| **ฟ้าผ่าเงียบ** | Made-up combination |
| Any idiom you're not 100% sure about | Risk of embarrassment |

**Rule:** When in doubt, leave it out.

---

#### 📋 Idiom Usage Guidelines

**Minimum:** 1-2 verified idioms per article
**Maximum:** 4-5 (more than this feels forced)
**Placement:** 
- 1 in opening hook (emotional anchor)
- 1-2 in pivot/turning point
- 1 in closing (if natural)

