### 🌡️ WARMTH RESTORATION PASS — NEW in v1.7

**CORE PRINCIPLE:**
> After applying all accuracy filters, do ONE final pass to restore conversational warmth.

**The Problem v1.7 Solves:**
> v1.6 filters made content more accurate but slightly more formal. This pass restores human warmth without sacrificing accuracy.

---

#### Warmth Checklist (Run After All Other Filters)

**1. ครับ/ค่ะ Frequency:**
- [ ] At least 3 natural uses of "ครับ" or "ค่ะ"
- [ ] Not mechanical (every sentence) but natural rhythm
- [ ] Appears in watermarks and personal moments

**2. Direct Address:**
- [ ] At least 2 uses of "คุณ" addressing reader directly
- [ ] At least 1 "ลองนึกภาพ..." or "ลองคิดดู..."
- [ ] Reader feels spoken TO, not AT

**3. Rhetorical Questions:**
- [ ] At least 1 rhetorical question in body
- [ ] Example: "ถ้าคุณอยู่ในสถานการณ์นี้ จะทำยังไง?"
- [ ] Creates mental engagement

**4. Emotional Anchor in First 100 Words:**
- [ ] Hook contains emotional element
- [ ] Reader FEELS something before data appears
- [ ] Not just facts — there's a human in the story

**5. Personal Aside:**
- [ ] At least 1 "ผมเข้าใจครับว่า..." moment
- [ ] Shows empathy, not just expertise
- [ ] Breaks the "lecture" feeling

---

#### Quick Warmth Fixes

| If Output Feels... | Add This |
|--------------------|----------|
| Too formal/stiff | Personal aside: "ผมเข้าใจครับว่าฟังดูน่ากลัว แต่..." |
| Like a lecture | Rhetorical question: "คุณเคยรู้สึกแบบนี้ไหม?" |
| Distant | Direct address: "และนั่นคือสิ่งที่คุณต้องรู้" |
| Cold | Emotional beat: "พอเห็นตัวเลขนี้ ผมก็ใจหายเหมือนกันครับ" |

